President Obama and his wife Michelle send their best wishes to Muslims celebrating Eid al-Adha and congratulate those participating in the Hajj pilgrimage. They acknowledge the diversity of the Muslim community and emphasize the importance of unity and equality among people of different backgrounds. The President also praises the tradition of charitable giving during Eid and highlights the shared values of the Abrahamic faiths. He extends warm greetings on behalf of the American people and hopes that the prayers for peace made by the Hajj pilgrims and people of all faiths are answered.